                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3690: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-29T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 29, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 29—4:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Japanese naval units now at Shanghai comprise: 17 destroyers, 4 cruisers, 1
                    aircraft carrier, 1 gunboat. Of these units 12 destroyers and 1 cruiser arrived
                    yesterday.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
